The paper deals with algorithms for generating random spanning trees from an edge-weighted undirected graph, which is a problem in graph theory and combinatorial optimization. The use of effective resistance metric and Gaussian elimination suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The approximation procedure for computing effective resistances and the error correction procedure suggest that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the focus on sampling and probability distributions suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
